# SCM Workflow

## Branching

- **Default branch:** `main`
- **Workflow:** GitFlow with semantic versioning
- **Feature work:** Always on feature branches created from `main`

## Feature Branches

- Work off feature branches (e.g. `feature/add-npc-profiles`) created from `main`
- **Before starting new work:** Ask the user if they want to create a new feature branch
- **When merging:** On user request, push to `main` and delete the feature branch

## Semantic Versioning

- Use [SemVer](https://semver.org/): `MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH`
- Bump version in `package.json` when releasing
- Tag releases: `git tag v1.0.0`

## Workflow Summary

1. Create feature branch from `main` when starting new work (ask first)
2. Work and commit on the feature branch
3. On user request: merge to `main`, push, delete feature branch
